    subgraph "Cost Optimization Strategies"
        J1["Lambda Optimization:
        ✅ Right-size memory (CPU scales with memory)
        ✅ Reduce package size (<50MB)
        ✅ Use Provisioned Concurrency only if needed
        ✅ Implement caching (reduce invocations)"]

        J2["Fargate Optimization:
        ✅ Use Fargate Spot for fault-tolerant workloads
        ✅ Right-size vCPU and memory
        ✅ Use Graviton2 (arm64) for 20% savings
        ✅ Implement auto-scaling"]

        J3["EC2 Optimization:
        ✅ Reserved Instances for baseline
        ✅ Spot for batch/fault-tolerant
        ✅ Auto-scaling for variable load
        ✅ Hibernate instead of stop (save EBS)"]
    end

    subgraph "Real-World Examples"
        K1["Netflix
        Architecture: 700+ microservices
        Mix: 70% EC2 (RIs), 20% Lambda, 10% Fargate
        Strategy: Right tool for right job
        Result: $100M+ annual savings"]

        K2["Coca-Cola (Freestyle App)
        Before: EC2 instances (always-on)
        After: Lambda + API Gateway
        Result: 60% cost reduction, $13K → $5K/month"]

        K3["Thomson Reuters
        Workload: Document processing
        Before: EMR cluster 24/7 ($12K/month)
        After: Lambda + Step Functions (on-demand)
        Result: 90% cost reduction ($12K → $1.2K/month)"]
    end

    subgraph "Hidden Costs"
        L1["Serverless Hidden Costs:
        - Data transfer: $0.09/GB outbound
        - NAT Gateway: $0.045/hour + $0.045/GB
        - CloudWatch Logs: $0.50/GB ingested
        - VPC endpoints: $0.01/hour"]

        L2["EC2 Hidden Costs:
        - EBS volumes: $0.10/GB-month
        - Load balancers: $18/month + data processing
        - Data transfer: $0.09/GB outbound
        - Elastic IPs: $3.60/month if unattached"]
    end

